"a.漫不经心的 【英】 adj. 漫不经心的(unconcer ned) adj. 无忧无虑的; 漠不关心的 = unconcerned = nonchalant 【记】in不, souci使烦恼, ant: 不会烦恼－漫不经心的souci是日本的外来语读: 寿司(一种美味食品)在in寿司souci上的蚂蚁ant－有好吃的, 所以无忧无虑的 【类】tenacious: yield = insouciant: worry不屈不挠的不会屈服 = 无忧无虑的不会担忧 【记】in 无 + soul 灵魂，心灵，精神→没魂的，没心的→不关心的；近于in 不 + solicit 恳求 【相关】soul 灵魂，心灵，精神 insouciant (adj.)  1829, from French insouciant ""careless, thoughtless, heedless,"" from in- ""not"" (see in- (1)) + souciant ""caring,"" present participle of soucier ""to care,"" from Latin sollicitare ""to agitate"" (see solicit). Related: Insouciantly."
